        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Atlanta</placeName> <date>Apl 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1854</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I received the Box sent<lb/> to my address after some delay&#44; but up<lb/> to this time I have not distributed the<lb/> Bibles strictly in accordance with your<lb/> instructions&#44; as an opportunity offered to<lb/> dispose of Two. I have taken the liberty of fur&#61;<lb/>&#61;nishing the parties&#44; and it is likely I shall<lb/> sell one or two more&#8212;at all events the <persName>Revd<lb/> I. Shaty<add>&#63;</add></persName> shall be furnished with his copy&#44;<lb/> as I learn he is about leaving <placeName>Augusta</placeName>.<lb/> If <del>it be</del> necessary I will advise you of<lb/> more are required to furnish your subscribers<lb/> through me&#8212;<persName>Col Mitchell</persName> is absent from<lb/> <placeName>Athens</placeName>&#44; but I shall send his copy by the<lb/> first opportunity. I think a <persName>Mr <add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> will take a copy as soon as he returns<lb/> home&#44; as he has expressed great anxiety<lb/> to have one&#44; but has been absent since<lb/> I have been in receipt of them.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed please find check<lb/> on <placeName>New York</placeName> for amts collected on yr.<lb/> account. <persName>A I Brady</persName> Bible &#36;9. subscr &#36;6 &#36;15.<lb/> <persName>I Mayer</persName> subscript &#36;11. <persName>Frankford</persName> &#36;6. 12<lb/> <persName>Brown</persName> &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Do&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#36;6 &#160;&#160;&#160;<persName>Lazarus</persName>.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#36;6. 12.<lb/> <persName>Lazaron</persName> 1 Bible &#36;8. <persName role="author">A Alexander</persName> Balance &#38; Subscription &#36;8. 26<lb/> <persName role="author">A Alexander</persName> 1 Bible 9<lb/> &#189; pr ct premium on check 37 &#36;73.63&#47;100 &#36;74</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><persName>Mr I. Mayer</persName> has taken a Bible c &#36;9.00<lb/> which please charge him with&#44; as soon<lb/> as I can sell the others or collect for you<lb/> a check shall be sent. I wish it was in my<lb/> power to assist you in your Payments&#44; but<lb/> times are so dull that it is extremely diffi<lb/>&#45;cult for me to get on with my own&#44; as we<lb/> have no facility for getting money apart<lb/> from sales&#44; as collections cannot be made</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You will please charge me with the<lb/> Prayer Books as I cannot spare the amt<lb/> for them at the present. I fear <persName>Dia&#39;s</persName><lb/> Letters will not sell in <placeName>Atlanta</placeName>&#44; as I<lb/> cannot induce any of our people to take<lb/> a copy&#44; and of course those of the adverse<lb/> faith will not. I delivered your message<lb/> to <persName>Mr Mayer</persName>&#44; and no doubt under the cir&#61;<lb/>cumstances he will excuse you for not<lb/> replying. You will please excuse all errors<lb/> as I have no clerk and am obliged to have<lb/> the titles and wait upon all customers<lb/> who present themselves. <persName>Mrs. A.</persName> <add>&#63;</add> <persName>Mrs B.</persName><lb/> and all your friends unite in presenting<lb/> to you their kind regards&#44; and with the<lb/> tender of my services in what ever way<lb/> you can make them available</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">I am yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">A. Alexander</persName></p>
			<p>I have no time to write</p>
			<p>and correct my letters</p>
			<p>so take this for what</p>
			<p>it may be worth</p>
          
        </body>
